author: Inside Edition
description: Samantha Stites was stalked for 13 years, then held captive inside a soundproof bunker. Her story is featured in the new Hulu documentary "Stalking Samantha: 13 Years of Terror." She spoke with Inside Edition's Alison Hall. Stites’ stalker, Christopher Thomas, first encountered her at a church group in Michigan, where she attended college. One night, Thomas broke into Stites' home and abducted her, taking her to a bunker he made that  he said was inspired by the TV series "You."
title: Samantha Stites Speaks Out After Her Abduction

author: Inside Edition
description: Chilling just-released video shows a Walmart knife rampage. The footage shows unsuspecting shoppers being ambushed by the attacker one after another. After stabbing  multiple people, the man ran for the exit to the parking lot. There, he was confronted by two Marine veterans who cornered him in the parking lot in Traverse City, police said. All eleven victims survived.
title: Just-Released Video Shows Knife Attack Inside Michigan Walmart

author: Inside Edition
description: Video captured the moment police handcuffed a top prosecutor in a ritzy Newport, Rhode Island nightspot. Devon Flanagan, a special assistant attorney general, was being put in a police car as she allegedly threatened a police officer. Her friend, Veronica Hannan was also arrested. Flanagan and Hannan were having a night out at Clarke Cooke House. Authorities say they were asked to leave. When they didn't, the police were called.
title: Top Prosecutor and Exec Arrested in Rhode Island

author: Inside Edition
description: A man was posing for a picture with a shark he just caught when, in the blink of an eye, the predator bit back. Shawn Muese and his friends caught a 6-foot lemon shark on the beach in Boca Grande, Florida. Lemon sharks have teeth that are razor sharp. The fire department arrived in three minutes. Muese had to be hospitalized, but says the gnarly bite is healing. He has a message for the shark that bit him and got away: "See you next time."
title: Man Taking Photo With Captured Shark Goes Wrong

author: Inside Edition
description: Inside Edition traveled to an island once owned by convicted pedophile Jeffrey Epstein with the man who was once his personal boat captain. The notorious Caribbean hideaway is back in the spotlight. Guy Dohm said he ferried Epstein to and from the island. At the time, Dohm said he assumed the passengers were Epstein's wife and kids. It wasn't until later that he realized Epstein did not have a family.
title: Inside the Private Island Where Jeffrey Epstein Trafficked Teen Girls

author: Inside Edition
description: Eva Pilgrim completed her first day as the host of Inside Edition on Monday and she received many calls to congratulate her. On Tuesday morning, Pilgrim sat down with Gayle King and the co-anchors at “CBS Mornings” Pilgrim says she is very close to her mother, who suggested she wear a brighter, more colorful outfit on her second day. Pilgrim's 3-year-old daughter, Ella, also reviewed her mother’s debut.
title: Eva Pilgrim Congratulated After 1st Day Hosting Inside Edition

author: Inside Edition
description: If the contents of this truck were known, there would have been an all-out race to get to this highway fire. That's because it was hauling 40,000 pounds of ribeye steak. No injuries were reported, but officials say the shipment was a total loss. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 40,000 Pounds of Ribeye Go Up in Flames in Truck Fire on Missouri Highway

author: Inside Edition
description: New Jersey lifeguard Alex Kaus had the scare of her life this summer when she was impaled by a beach umbrella in a freak accident. Speaking exclusively with INSIDE EDITION, Alex said she was on shift at Ashbury Park Beach when the wind lifted her and the umbrella off her stand. “I landed on my feet with the umbrella poking through my back… I said, ‘I think I’ve been impaled,’ just like that.” INSIDE EDITION got the whole story and tagged along for a check-up with Alex’s doctor.
title: Teen Lifeguard Impaled By Beach Umbrella Speaks Out

author: Inside Edition
description: Nightmares can be an unpleasant side effect of getting much-needed sleep, but experts at the world's largest psychiatric hospital in England say they could be an indicator of what's really going on in our brains. Bad dreams are the focus of an art exhibit at the Bethlem Museum of the Mind. Many were created by patients and date back more than a century. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: British Museum Displays Artwork Inspired by Nightmares
